    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix EPS Quality of Service decoding due to operator precedence issue\n\n### Summary\nThe `decode_eps_quality_of_service` function in `EpsQualityOfService.c` incorrectly determines the presence of bit rate fields due to operator precedence in conditional expressions. This causes improper decoding of EPS QoS IEs when bit rates are present.\n\n### Issue Description\nIn the `decode_eps_quality_of_service` function, the conditional expressions that determine whether bitRates and bitRatesExt are present have incorrect operator precedence:\n\n```c\n// Incorrect - evaluated as: if ( ielen > (2 + (iei > 0)) ? 1 : 0 )\nif ( ielen > 2 + (iei > 0) ? 1 : 0 ) {\n\n// Incorrect - evaluated as: if ( ielen > (6 + (iei > 0)) ? 1 : 0 )\nif ( ielen > 6 + (iei > 0) ? 1 : 0 ) {\n```\n\nThis leads to incorrect evaluation of whether bit rate fields are present in the EPS QoS IE, causing:\n- Bit rate fields to be skipped when they should be decoded\n- Potential buffer overreads when attempting to decode non-existent extended bit rates\n- Incorrect QoS parameter handling in NAS procedures\n\n### Reproduction\nThe issue manifests when processing NAS messages containing EPS Quality of Service IEs with bit rate information. Observable symptoms include:\n- Incomplete EPS QoS parameter decoding\n- Potential segmentation faults when processing malformed or incomplete QoS IEs\n- Incorrect bearer setup due to missing bit rate information\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/COMMON/IES/EpsQualityOfService.c`: Added parentheses to fix operator precedence in conditional expressions (lines 61 and 71)\n"
}